  "text": "Theoretically, if three values for x and y are available, then the values of each unknown coefficient can be found in both of the above two cases. What is important, nevertheless, is that in each case there are 2N+1 unknowns to be determined. It is preferable if all the unknowns can be found simultaneously. Let us first review the solution to the simpler three (nonlinear or linear) equations in three unknowns, nonlinear for equation [CITATION_1] and linear for equation [CITATION_2] .",
